    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-22T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-22T06:00:00-05:00" n="414"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659.119/391</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-22T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1918, noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.05 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2554. The published four months’ commercial agreement between Denmark and the
                    Central Powers as from August 1 is as follows:</p>
                <p>Denmark contributes foodstuffs at increased prices, receiving in return promised
                    compensation in salt, iron, coal, potash, petroleum, etc., in return for an
                    extra quantity of butter. Germany has promised an extra supply of benzine for
                    the Danish fisheries. No quantities were fixed for the foodstuffs to be exported
                    to Germany; the amounts to depend upon the exportable surplus available. Copy to
                    London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
